# Keep the build context to what the Dockerfile actually needs.
#
# node_modules is the load-bearing entry. pnpm installs a symlink farm pointing
# into a store outside the package, so copying a host's node_modules into the
# image replaces the freshly installed modules with links that resolve to
# nothing — `nest build` then fails with "Cannot find module @nestjs/cli".
# It only bites when building from a working copy that has been installed in
# (a fresh `git clone`, as on the GPU VM, has none), which makes it exactly the
# kind of failure that shows up on someone else's machine and not in CI.
node_modules/
**/node_modules/

# Build output — the image builds its own.
dist/
build/
.svelte-kit/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Never let a local env file reach an image layer.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

.git/
.github/
.idea/
.vscode/
.claude/

# Runtime scratch, not inputs.
staging/
cache/
coverage/
**/.staging/
**/.cache/

# Not needed to build or run the server.
docs/
*.md
!apps/backend/README.md
